sourceBlocks.text: I am writing to appl for the STEM Intern position in summer 2026 at the NASA IV&V Facility. Having been a summer intern once at TMC corporate and once at NASA, I have proven experience in developing containerized agentic AI workflows, with parts of my work having gone into production at IV&V after reiews and refactoring.

During my summer 2025 internship, I develped full-stack applications for agentic AI workflow testing and development with React, Node.js, Python, and AI APIs, within Docker environments as needed, meeting requirements and knowledge capture goals. A substantial piece of my work was the requirements analysis pipeline, using a layered agent approach with self-validation. I also helped configure LibreChat, which is now being used as the central chat interface for the facility. Beyond development, I led knowledge sharing sessions which demonstrated to the team how to use agentic coding tools, which are now being heavily used in the facility. These experiences gave me a clear understanding of the expectations of NASA IV&V and how to contribute effectively in the work environment.

Since my last internship, I have been working on various classes at WVU which complement my previous experience, such as Softare Engineering, Principles of Programming Languages, and Computer Systems Concepts. My academic experience and previous work experience in the facility position me as an effective member and contributor from day one. I am excited to continue pushing the frontier of AI with the team, and to contribute meaningful research, knowledge sharing, testing, and development.

I am confident that returning to the facility for a second summer will provide even greater value to IV&V, now having relevant previous experience. I welcome discussion on how I can contribute to the work at NASA IV&V. Feel free to contact me at 304-685-1622 or aaron.williams.wv777@gmail.com to schedule a conversation. Thank you for your time and consideration.
